cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with visualisation techniques for image classification models learnt using deep Convolutional Networks (ConvNets). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of these techniques for weakly supervised object segmentation, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also establishes a connection between the gradient-based ConvNet visualisation methods and deconvolutional networks, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the application of these techniques in multimedia, which is related to cs.MM (Multimedia).
